29/03/2006
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- During a visit to Ljubljana on Tuesday (28 March), Macedonian Minister for Local Self-Government Rizvan Sulejmani said his country was willing to accept Slovenian expertise in decentralisation reforms and the utilisation of EU funds. Sulejmani and Slovenian counterpart Ivan Zagar also agreed to intensify bilateral co-operation in terms of regional development. 
In other news, a new Macedonian political formation, the Party for European Future, was formed Tuesday. The party, comprised largely of intellectuals and members of the business community, describes itself as multiethnic and pro-European. It plans to run in the parliamentary elections later this year. (Makfax - 28/03/06)
